    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102746</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>Jada is mixing powdered soap with water to create a cleaning solution for the school car wash. The instructions say to use 2 capfulls of soap for every 5 cups of water. Solve the following problems. Explain or show your reasoning. If you get stuck, consider creating a table.</p>

<ol>
	<li>If Jada uses 30 cups of water, how much soap will she use?</li>
	<li>If Jada uses 8 capfulls of soap, how much water will she use?</li>
	<li>If Jada uses 1 capfull of soap, how much water will she use?</li>
</ol>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><p>Answers vary. Sample response:&#xA0;</p>

<table border="1">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th scope="col">soap (capfulls)</th>
			<th scope="col">water (cups)</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td>2</td>
			<td>5</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>12</td>
			<td>30</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>8</td>
			<td>20</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>1</td>
			<td><span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="3217">\(1\frac12\)</span></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<ol>
	<li>12 capfulls, because 5 times 6 is 30, and 2 times 6 is 12.</li>
	<li>20 cups, because 2 times 4 is 8, and 5 times 4 is 20.</li>
	<li>
<span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="3217">\(1\frac12\)</span> cups, because half of 2 is 1 and half of 5 is <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="3217">\(1\frac12\)</span>.</li>
</ol>
</div>
